</div>
<div class="comment" id="comment-47778048">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/ZoomZoomZoom">ZoomZoomZoom</a> 2 hours ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">I&#x27;m all for Win32, but those odd-shapes and custom skins were the precursors and the normalizing precedent for the current default mentality of &quot;visual identity = branding&quot; that&#x27;s been killing desktop computing experience for years and is one of the reasons we have to endure reacts, electrons and multitude of half-baked widget libraries that consist of things looking like no particular control but all feature blurry text rendering, flaky accessibility, negative information density and their own special sets of bugs.<p>Unless you&#x27;re building a Blender or an Ardour or, I don&#x27;t know, a trading platform or a game, an individualized GUI should be the last of your priorities.</div>
