<div class="comment" id="comment-47777751">
  <div class="comment_head"><a href="/user/okanat">okanat</a> 3 hours ago</div>
  <div class="comment_text">&gt;  freaking memory is 77% full when freaking Windows 11 starts up.<p>Unused memory is wasted memory. 77% is basically caches + private process memory + shared memory. Unless you are comparing by the private committed working set, you usually have no idea of the actual usage. .Net apps and browsers often allocate overcommitted memory to avoid making system calls.<p>I get it, using browsers for ToDo apps is slow, however measuring their impact is harder than you think. At the same time the best x-platform UI framework is the browser. Qt comes next but it lacks man-decade amount of fixes&#x2F;polishing to match native font support and text rendering, media handling, accessibility support, hw acceleration and memory pressure behaviors of Skia and Chromium.</div>
